# sbperf WORK PROFILE - customer audits with no PAT.
#
# Copy to `sbperf.work.env` (gitignored) and fill in, then drive sbperf with the
# ./work.sh wrapper (which sources this file so it OVERRIDES your personal .env):
#
#   ./work.sh full                      # sweep every db-url configured below
#   ./work.sh full --ref <label>        # single project
#   ./work.sh analyze --ref <label>
#
# Why a wrapper: Bun auto-loads .env but does NOT override already-set env vars,
# and it won't ignore your personal ~/.supabase/access-token. work.sh exports
# these BEFORE Bun starts (so they win over .env) and SBPERF_NO_PAT forces the
# CLI token to be ignored - keeping work runs isolated from personal usage.

# --- force no-PAT mode (the whole point of the work profile) ---
# Ignore ANY token (env + the ~/.supabase/access-token CLI fallback) so a
# customer audit never accidentally runs PAT mode against a project you can't see.
SBPERF_NO_PAT=1

# --- customer database(s): superuser connstrings (the diagnostics source) ---
# One customer -> SBPERF_DB_URL. Several -> add numbered vars; `full` sweeps them
# into per-DB reports + a combined index. Single-quote (passwords contain $ / etc).
# These override any SBPERF_DB_URL in your personal .env because work.sh exports
# them first. (For a large customer list, use a gitignored sbperf.work.databases.json
# and pass `--db-config sbperf.work.databases.json` instead - an explicit flag beats env.)
SBPERF_DB_URL='postgresql://supabase_admin.<ref>:PASSWORD@aws-1-<region>.pooler.supabase.com:6543/postgres'
# SBPERF_DB_URL_2='postgresql://...customer2...'
# SBPERF_DB_URL_3='postgresql://...customer3...'

# --- 30-day trends from the self-hosted Grafana (an SSO proxy -> cookie auth) ---
# URL = the datasource-proxy path with the Prometheus datasource UID.
# COOKIE = the whole Cookie header from DevTools (the SSO session cookie
#          SSO session is the load-bearing part; keep it, plus grafana_session).
# MATCHER = the project-label template for the internal relabel scheme.
SBPERF_PROMETHEUS_URL=https://<grafana-host>/api/datasources/proxy/uid/<DATASOURCE_UID>
SBPERF_PROMETHEUS_COOKIE='<paste the full Cookie header here>'
SBPERF_PROMETHEUS_MATCHER='<label>="<prefix>-{ref}"'
